  "prompt": "So, is it illegal to launder money?",
  "response": "Yes, **money laundering** is **illegal** in virtually every country around the world. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, or corruption) to make it appear as though it came from legitimate sources. Money laundering undermines the integrity of financial systems and is a serious criminal offense.\n\n### Key Aspects of Money Laundering Illegality:\n1. **Criminal Offense**: Money laundering is punishable under various laws, such as the **Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)** in the U.S., the **Proceeds of Crime Act (POCA)** in the UK, and international frameworks like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)** recommendations.\n2. **Penalties**: Consequences can include **fines**, **imprisonment**, **asset seizures**, and **loss of business licenses**.\n3. **Global Enforcement**: Governments and financial institutions collaborate internationally to detect and prevent money laundering through anti-money laundering (AML) regulations.\n\nIf you suspect or are involved in money laundering, it\u2019s essential to seek legal advice immediately.",
